    <!-- Main Content -->
    <main class="pt-32 pb-24 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
            
            <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-gray-500 mb-12 animate-fade-in-up">
                <a href="https://bluv-developer.github.io/RCSO-Bot/" class="hover:text-brand-accent transition-colors">Home</a>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-right text-xs"></i>
                <span class="text-white font-bold">Supervisor Guide</span>
            </div>

            <!-- Header -->
            <div class="text-center mb-16 space-y-6 animate-fade-in-up">
                <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold">
                    Official Supervisor <span class="text-gradient">Procedures</span>
                </h1>
                <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg max-w-4xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
                    This official guide outlines the critical steps and required actions for Command Staff (Sergeant+) using the RCSO Bot's advanced management systems. These procedures ensure accountability, consistency, and proper record-keeping across the department.
                </p>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Detailed Procedures -->
            <div class="space-y-12">

                <!-- Section I: Report Review & Approval Protocol -->
                <section class="section-box animate-fade-in-up">
                    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold section-title flex items-center gap-3">
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-file-check command-icon"></i> I. Report Review and Approval Protocol
                    </h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">
                        All formal reports filed by officers are automatically posted to the dedicated **RECORDS** channel, initiating a review thread. Command staff must check these threads regularly and take action using the interactive buttons provided by the bot.
                    </p>
                    
                    <ol class="procedure-list ml-4">
                        <li class="text-white">
                            <p class="text-lg font-medium text-brand-accent mb-1">Review Report Content</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
                                Open the report thread in the RECORDS channel. Carefully review the content, including the submitted charges, incident narrative, and officer details. Verify the report adheres to all current departmental policy and accuracy standards.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="text-white">
                            <p class="text-lg font-medium text-brand-accent mb-1">Take Approval Action</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
                                If the report is valid, click the <span class="cmd">APPROVE</span> button within the thread. This action confirms the report's validity. For Booking (Arrest) reports, approval automatically sends the finalized record to the **JAIL_LOG** channel. The bot locks the thread upon approval.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="text-white">
                            <p class="text-lg font-medium text-brand-accent mb-1">Take Denial Action</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
                                If the report contains errors or is invalid, click the <span class="cmd">DENY</span> button. The bot will lock the thread. Following denial, supervisors must contact the filing officer outside the bot system (via direct message or separate channel) to explain the error and instruct them to file a corrected report using the <span class="cmd">/report_panel</span>.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </section>

                <!-- Section II: Personnel Disciplinary Actions -->
                <section class="section-box animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay: 0.1s;">
                    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold section-title flex items-center gap-3">
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-gavel command-icon"></i> II. Personnel Disciplinary Actions
                    </h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">
                        These restricted commands are used to enforce departmental standards. The system automatically handles role changes, logging, and timed restoration of status. Ensure your rank authorizes these actions.
                    </p>
                    
                    <ol class="procedure-list ml-4">
                        <li class="text-white">
                            <p class="text-lg font-medium text-brand-accent mb-1">Suspension Procedure</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
                                Execute <span class="cmd">/suspend [user] [reason]</span>. The bot will automatically apply the SUSPENDED role and remove all previous departmental roles (excluding default/managed roles). The suspension period is fixed at **3 days**, after which the bot automatically restores the user's previous roles. The action is logged publicly and provides an <span class="cmd">UNDO</span> button for immediate reversal.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="text-white">
                            <p class="text-lg font-medium text-brand-accent mb-1">Discharge Procedure</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
                                Execute <span class="cmd">/discharge [user] [reason]</span> for final separation. The bot removes all roles and applies the DISCHARGED role for a **24-hour hold**. This is the final and permanent personnel action. A public log is created with an <span class="cmd">UNDO</span> button for immediate reversal if required due to administrative error.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="text-white">
                            <p class="text-lg font-medium text-brand-accent mb-1">Logging Minor Infractions</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
                                Execute <span class="cmd">/infraction [user] [reason]</span>. This is used for recording minor issues or verbal warnings. The action is logged in the **INFRACTION** channel for personnel history without changing the user's active roles or status.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </section>

                <!-- Section III: Training & FTO Oversight -->
                <section class="section-box animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay: 0.2s;">
                    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold section-title flex items-center gap-3">
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-microphone command-icon"></i> III. Training and FTO Oversight
                    </h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">
                        Supervisors must ensure training procedures are followed correctly, although most of the time tracking is automatic.
                    </p>
                    
                    <ol class="procedure-list ml-4">
                        <li class="text-white">
                            <p class="text-lg font-medium text-brand-accent mb-1">Monitoring FTO Logs</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
                                The bot automatically tracks time spent in the **TRAINING_VC**. Supervisors review the final logs sent to the **FTO_LOG** channel. This feature requires no direct supervisor commands. The system ensures only active training time is logged by pausing the timer if the FTO or trainee mutes or deafens their mic.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="text-white">
                            <p class="text-lg font-medium text-brand-accent mb-1">Verifying Training Results</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
                                Instructors use the <span class="cmd">/training_panel</span> to submit results (Pass/Fail) for cadets. Supervisors are responsible for checking the **TRAINING_RES** channel periodically to ensure that all sessions and results are correctly filed by instructors immediately upon session completion.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </section>
                
                <!-- Section IV: Manual Rank Adjustment (Admin Only) -->
                <section class="section-box animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay: 0.3s;">
                    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold section-title flex items-center gap-3">
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-ranking-star command-icon"></i> IV. Manual Rank Adjustment (Admin Only)
                    </h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">
                        These commands are strictly reserved for server Administrators (High Command) to manually adjust rank roles. All actions are logged for audit purposes.
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="space-y-4 ml-4">
                        <div class="text-white">
                            <p class="text-lg font-medium text-brand-accent mb-1">Promotion</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
                                Execute <span class="cmd">/promote [member] [rank]</span>. This grants the specified rank role to the target member. The action is logged in the dedicated **PROMOTION** channel.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="text-white">
                            <p class="text-lg font-medium text-brand-accent mb-1">Demotion</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
                                Execute <span class="cmd">/demote [member] [rank]</span>. This removes the specified rank role from the target member. The action is logged in the dedicated **DEMOTION** channel.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>


                <!-- Section V: FAQ (Frequently Asked Questions) -->
                <section class="section-box animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay: 0.4s;">
                    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold section-title flex items-center gap-3">
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-circle-question command-icon"></i> V. Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)
                    </h2>
                    
                    <div class="space-y-6">
                        <div class="text-white">
                            <p class="text-xl font-medium text-brand-accent mb-1">Q: Why are my commands being denied?</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
                                A: Most restricted commands require the "Manage Messages" permission or higher (for non-admin actions like suspension) or full Administrator permissions (for promotion/demotion). Verify your rank role has the necessary permissions. Also, remember you cannot discipline a user whose top role is equal to or higher than your own rank.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="text-white">
                            <p class="text-xl font-medium text-brand-accent mb-1">Q: An officer submitted a faulty report. What do I do?</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
                                A: Use the <span class="cmd">DENY</span> button on the report thread. This archives the faulty record. You must then privately message the officer to explain the mistake and have them use the <span class="cmd">/report_panel</span> to file a corrected version.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="text-white">
                            <p class="text-xl font-medium text-brand-accent mb-1">Q: How do I manually restore a suspended officer?</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
                                A: If you need to manually restore an officer before the 3-day timer expires, locate the original public log message for the suspension and click the <span class="cmd">UNDO</span> button. This instantly restores their roles and clears the active punishment flag in the bot's system.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

            </div>
        </div>
